<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-759-178  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 759 178.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Robotics and Automation  August 1989 v5 n4p522(7).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Dynamic modeling of closed-chain robotic manipulators andimplications for trajectory control. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Murray, John J.; Lovell, Gilbert H.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A simple and computationally efficient method is developed for thedynamic modeling of manipulators with one or more closed kinematicloops.andP;  Such manipulators tend to be faster and more accurate thanopen-chain systems and, consequently, are finding growing favor inboth industrial and research applications.andP;  The new modelingmethod uses D'Alembert's principle to effect a transformation fromthe generalized dynamics of serial and open-chain systems to theclosed-chain manipulator model.andP;  The transformation furtherclarifies the relationship between closed-chain systems andreduced dynamics.andP;  The impacts of closed kinematic chains on robottrajectory control are discussed.andP;  Details of the development andimplementation of the modeling method are described.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ModelingDynamicsManipulatorsRobot ArmsMethods.andO;Feature:   illustrationtablechart.andO;Caption:   Closed-chain inverse dynamics. (table)The positioning subsystem. (chart)The reduced system. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>